#Approach:

Union of Two Sorted Arrays – Two Pointer Approach

Dono sorted arrays par do pointers i aur j rakho.
Dono arrays ko compare karo aur jo chhota element ho usse union list me add karo.
Agar dono elements equal ho to ek hi baar add karo aur dono pointers aage badhao.

Duplicate avoid karne ke liye check karo ki jo element add kar rahe ho
wo last added element ke equal na ho.

Agar ek array khatam ho jaye to dusre array ke remaining elements add kar do
(lekin duplicate check ke saath).

Time Complexity: O(n1 + n2)
Space Complexity: O(n1 + n2) for union array

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] unionArray(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        int n1 = nums1.length;
        int n2 = nums2.length;
        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;
        List<Integer> unionList = new ArrayList<>();

        while(i < n1 && j < n2){
            if(nums1[i] < nums2[j]){
                if(unionList.size() == 0 || unionList.get(unionList.size() - 1) != nums1[i]){
                    unionList.add(nums1[i]);
                }
                i++;
            }else if(nums1[i] > nums2[j]){
                if(unionList.size() == 0 || unionList.get(unionList.size() - 1) != nums2[j]){
                    unionList.add(nums2[j]);
                }
                j++;
            }
            else{ //when both are equal
                if(unionList.size() == 0 || unionList.get(unionList.size() - 1) != nums1[i]){
                    unionList.add(nums1[i]);
                }
                i++;
                j++;
            }
        }

        //if nums2 gets exhausted and nums1 remained
        while(i<n1){
            if(unionList.size() == 0 || unionList.get(unionList.size() - 1) != nums1[i]){
                unionList.add(nums1[i]);
            }
            i++;
        }

        //if nums1 gets exhausted and nums2 remained
        while(j<n2){
            if(unionList.size() == 0 || unionList.get(unionList.size() - 1) != nums2[j]){
                unionList.add(nums2[j]);
            }
            j++;
        }

        int[] arr = new int[unionList.size()];
        for(int i=0; i<unionList.size(); i++){
            arr[i] = unionList.get(i);
        }

        return arr;
    }
}
